title: hash.h build error with MSVC
body_html:
@apaszke , @peterjc123

Hi,
I ran into the following compilation error using MSVC2015 Update 3
(using the latest pytorch version 31af836)

python_arg_flatten.h(44): note: see reference to function template instantiation 'size_t torch::get_hash<std::string,std::vector<torch::jit::python::IODescriptor::VariableMetadata,std::allocator<_Ty>>>(const std::string &,const std::vector<_Ty,std::allocator<_Ty>> &)' being compiled
with
[
_Ty=torch::jit::python::IODescriptor::VariableMetadata
]

torch/csrc/utils/hash.h(79): error C2668: 'torch::_hash_detail::dispatch_hash': ambiguous call to overloaded function

torch/csrc/utils/hash.h(69): note: could be 'size_t torch::_hash_detail::dispatch_hash(const T &)'
with
[
T=torch::jit::python::IODescriptor::VariableMetadata
]
torch/csrc/utils/hash.h(58): note: or 'unsigned __int64 torch::_hash_detail::dispatch_hash(const T &)'
with
[
T=torch::jit::python::IODescriptor::VariableMetadata
]

torch/csrc/utils/hash.h(79): note: while trying to match the argument list '(const torch::jit::python::IODescriptor::VariableMetadata)'

body:
@apaszke , @peterjc123

Hi,
I ran into the following compilation error using MSVC2015 Update 3
(using the latest pytorch version 31af8364121b0a92bd8ef32cdfdba8cfd5c2e451)


**python_arg_flatten.h(44):** note: see reference to function template instantiation 'size_t torch::get_hash<std::string,std::vector<torch::jit::python::IODescriptor::VariableMetadata,std::allocator<_Ty>>>(const std::string &,const std::vector<_Ty,std::allocator<_Ty>> &)' being compiled
        with
        [
            _Ty=torch::jit::python::IODescriptor::VariableMetadata
        ]

**torch/csrc/utils/hash.h(79):** error C2668: 'torch::_hash_detail::dispatch_hash': ambiguous call to overloaded function

**torch/csrc/utils/hash.h(69):** note: could be 'size_t torch::_hash_detail::dispatch_hash<T>(const T &)'
        with
        [
            T=torch::jit::python::IODescriptor::VariableMetadata
        ]
**torch/csrc/utils/hash.h(58)**: note: or  'unsigned __int64 torch::_hash_detail::dispatch_hash<T>(const T &)'
        with
        [
            T=torch::jit::python::IODescriptor::VariableMetadata
        ]

**torch/csrc/utils/hash.h(79)**: note: while trying to match the argument list '(const torch::jit::python::IODescriptor::VariableMetadata)'
